</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/02 9:38:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=493.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting in The Grey?</span><hr size=1> In my opinion:<br><br>Scarlet Desert zoneline is fit for only group pulling.  Most mobs I've seen there are static and there seems to be a rockfiend perpertually up staring right at the entrance.  To close for my taste as the closest wanderor stops behind him.<br><br>Mons Letalis zoneline is nicer.  As you exit, the right side of the exit is best for group pulling.  The wander mobs in the flats can run straight up to the hill with little risk of social aggro.  The left side is nice for quadding as it is a valley with no roamers in it.<br><br>How I do it:<br>  Bind in ML outside The Grey zoneline.  Spell setup is Volatic Draught (fire and cold get resisted alot), Pillar of Lightning, snare of choice, root of choice, Invisiblility, and Gate.  I have JBoots, but use what you deem necassary.  <br>  Use Invis (some snakes, some skeletons and the rare golem see invis while the rocktypes and worms do not.) to scout the flats and trip the traps.  Many mobs hide behind and occasionally IN the rocks (you'll see the tail every so often poking out).  Plan the pull to either avoid additional aggro (primarily rockfiends) or to gather up your mobs.  <br>  The Grey is a harsh mistress.  If I have 3 golems on the line and try to hunt down a 4th, more times than not I get a rockfiend addand have to abandon the quad.  Take what The Grey gives you and like it.<br><br> Golems run slow enough where you can quad without snaring them.  Unless you lagging or something is buggy, you can outrun snakes, golems, and rockfiends (all run at the same speed).  <br><br>At 54 with 230 INT, about 200 extra mana in items, FT 2, and Flappy (self-buffed only) I could easily quad golems and was a cast shy of quadding snakes.  When quadding I run them up on the hill heading away from ML zoneline then back along the valley once I reach the big rock near the corner.  With a KEI, I could quad snakes with ease and contemplated (but never tried) to single kite a rockfiend.<br><br>Fredre<br><br>P.S.  People running to ML from either SD or Ssra will train you and not think twice about it.  Keep on your toes.  I usually med on the hill to the left of ML (opposite the direction to go to SD) in chase cam mode so I can see the ML line.  Don't sit too close or mobs will aggro you from underneath and warp right onto you. Smack down will go from zero to 60 in 5.2 seconds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzothen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zothen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/02 2:03:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=493.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiting in The Grey?</span><hr size=1> How I used to quad the grey, but have moved on to quading worms, bats, monkeys, and vampires in ME.<br><br>Number 1<br><br>Get Aego, KEI, and Epic Skin, I would also suggest SoW/SoE<br><br>Number 2<br><br>Bind at SD zone line, and make sure to have gate up<br><br>Number 3<br><br>Zone into the grey, and shout a few times <br>&quot;Making BIG F$CKING TRAIN near SD, stay away&quot;<br><br>Number 4<br><br>Run around, and round up every skelly and rock fiend in that corner of the zone, should be like 50 to 60 skellies, and 4 to 8 fiends, once you have them all on you, run them in circle to pack them up, then run strait, and gate out<br><br>Number 5<br><br>Now, when you zone in, you have about 50 skellies all nicely packed, waiting for you to snare by the 4 and quad,and the fiends should be fare enough not to agro or you can do what I did, and just quad the fiends. All non static spawns will wonder away by the time you zone back in from gate.<br><br>Zothen <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=493.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=493.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=493.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=493.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=493.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=493.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm41">Interface Design<option value="gra